parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS actuator can cause the anti-lock braking system to malfunction, leading to loss of control of the vehicle or accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle's brakes pulsate or vibrate
the vehicle's brakes grab or jerk
the vehicle's brakes make a loud noise
and the vehicle's brakes feel soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid inverter can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Warning lights illuminate on the instrument panel
and the power inverter needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents, and compromising the safety of the vehicle, its occupants, and other road users.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause fires, as reported in one incident.
symptoms: the vehicle becomes engulfed in flames

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's braking intentions.
symptoms: The rear brake lights do not come on when the brake pedal is depressed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, and compromise the safety of the vehicle, its occupants, and other road users.
The failure of the 12-volt battery can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The 12-volt battery does not start the vehicle
the ignition does not turn over

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The slow intermittent drain on the auxiliary battery can cause the battery to die, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: and the dealer cannot identify the source of the battery draw.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The emission of noxious fumes into the cabin can cause discomfort, health issues, or even accidents due to driver distraction.
symptoms: The batteries charge and then start to emit noxious fumes (ozone) into the cabin when traveling downhill for extended periods.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor visibility of the instrument panel can cause driver distraction, accidents, or near-miss incidents.
symptoms: The speedometer is difficult to read during the daytime due to tinted lenses on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
Floor mat entrapment can cause unintended acceleration, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Accelerator pedal stuck under floor mat

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can cause unintended acceleration, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected acceleration when resuming cruise control

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Pedal misapplication can cause unintended acceleration, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Accelerator pedal caught under foot or shoe
